experiment: F-EMP3 Phase transition in empathic accuracy — concurrency scaling analysis
expect: Sharp phase transition in C-EDIT rate at some N_threshold. Linear or step-function collapse.
method: git log analysis S344-S352. Empathic accuracy proxy = 1 - (repair+harvest+fix commits / total). N_concurrent estimated from commit burst pattern and documented concurrency events.

threshold_effects.interpretation: First peer-modeling required — node must model ONE other session. Baseline empathic cost.
Empathic overload threshold — modeling 3+ peers simultaneously exceeds context capacity. ISO-13 anti-windup: cumulative coordination load.

phase_transition_verdict: FALSIFIED (strong sense) — no sharp discontinuous transition. CONFIRMED (weak sense) — two threshold effects at N=2 and N=4, not random.

c_edit_direct_evidence.S351_N5: 37.5% C-EDIT overhead (3 sessions trimmed L-544, all three attempted L-555/556 slot). Empathic failure type: PROJECTION — each node assumed others had NOT done the task (no alterity modeling). ISO-20 bounded epistemic replication applies.
c_edit_direct_evidence.L_557: C-EDIT documented as DUE-item convergence. All 3 C-EDIT types are empathic failures: CE-1=projection, CE-2=staging blindness, CE-3=resource blindness.

empathic_accuracy_metric_definition.name: Prediction-adjusted Repair Rate (PARR)
empathic_accuracy_metric_definition.limitation: Does not distinguish intentional harvest (positive) from failure-induced repair (negative). Future refinement: classify harvest as productive vs reactive.

f_emp4_connection.alterity_failure: At N≥3, C-EDIT events show all nodes PROJECTING self-state onto others: 'I need to trim L-544 → others haven't done it'. This is Stein's projection error — modeling the other as self, not as other.
f_emp4_connection.mechanism: Without claim.py, nodes have NO model of other nodes' current actions. Empathic accuracy is ZERO for concurrent actions — only sequential actions (via git log) are visible.

actual: Smooth degradation with two threshold effects (N=2, N=4). NOT a sharp phase transition. Empathic accuracy proxy shows -8.8pp per session added. C-EDIT events are measurable empathic failures (projection). PARR metric defined.
diff: Expected sharp phase transition — FALSIFIED. Got smooth degradation + thresholds. Unexpected: N=2 threshold is larger than N=3 threshold (first peer-modeling more costly than adding 3rd peer). The recovery at N=3 (S349 low overhead) shows stochastic component — empathic accuracy depends on WHICH sessions are concurrent, not just N.
next: Test PARR with claim.py active (S352+): does claim.py reduce repair rate at N=5? Also: F-EMP1 (NEXT.md prediction accuracy vs actual next-session actions) would give cleaner empathic measure than PARR.
